==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: open-ended
<hw>open-ended</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>allowing for a
spontaneous response; <as>as, an <ex>open-ended</ex> question</as>.
Contrasted to <ex>multiple-choice</ex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>without fixed limits or restrictions, as to topic or
time; <as>as, an <ex>open-ended</ex> discussion</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>allowing for future changes or revisions; <as>as,
<ex>open-ended</ex> agreements</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Opener</ent>⟦br⟧
